- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category as the paper proposes two algorithms for computing the Re-Pair grammar with improved space complexity. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also likely as the paper discusses the time complexity of the proposed algorithms. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the Re-Pair compression scheme is based on grammar induction and information theory. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is less likely but still possible as the Re-Pair compression scheme can be seen as a form of unsupervised learning. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also less likely but possible as the paper mentions the use of parallel computing to improve the time complexity of the algorithms.
